title: For Trade:  500 small pistol primers magnum for 45acp,44, 357,or 38 no 9mm
postcontent:
Wolf  small magnum pistol primers 5 100 ct boxes 

These will work fine for any large case cartridge that use small pistol primers as long as you don't load to max powder factor. I actually think they work better for 45acp than regular small primers  and Winchester only makes mag primers. 

Caution do not load 9mm with mag primers as the pressure is very high in the 9mm case and mag primers add 1500 lbs to whatever powder charge use. 

TULA primers are a little hard and ultra light trigger revolvers may need to hand primed.

title: Want To Buy:  Quality name brand AR15 lower receiver
postcontent: I am looking to buy quality, nationally recognized brands of lower receivers to build a few AR-15s.  If you are an FFL dealer, stop reading here.  I have no interest in buying from FFL dealers, I appreciate them all, but there is no point in leaving a trail of bread crumbs to my home so when a 'real' AWB eventually succeeds, Dianne Feinstein can come knocking on my door looking for my AR-15s.  I am only buying from other gun enthusiasts like myself, face to face, or shipped to me from within the state of NC, as is perfectly legal.  If you want a bill of sale, that is fine with me, draw one up, email it to me, I'll sign it and send it to you with my payment, but that is all you are getting unless you are local, then you can see my retired military I.D. too, but that is it, no driver's license, no state I.D., that is it.  If there is anything about my WTB ad that bothers you, do not contact me, or go ahead and flag the ad, that is how this site is set up to work.  If you think I'm asking someone to do something illegal, call the ATF (a department of Homeland Security), that is how our country works.  Don't get all butt hurt when they ignore you though, because like I said, I'm not asking anyone to do anything illegal, not even close to it.  That being said, I look forward to purchasing a few lower receivers, so let me know what you have.  I am a straight shooter, no bull, and expect to be treated the same.  Your idea of quality and mine probably differ, so just let me know what you have and the price you are asking, (ignore the price I have posted, I had to put something).  I'm building these for fun, so if you are looking to make your car, house, or rent payment with the profit you think you can make off of your lower receiver, don't bother contacting me.  A high price for a high quality lower is one thing, but otherwise, no, I don't think so, I don't care what the current political climate is.  I prefer stripped new lowers, but used in like new condition would work, even if they are already completed, that just means I'll have more time to build an upper.  Keep in mind, if it is already built, I have no idea what parts you have in it, or how much it has been fired, if used, so don't expect me to be wild about it.  When contacting me, send (good) pictures of what you are offering me, it'll make things go smoother.  Do not ask me what I will give you for it, I'm not bidding on an auction, I'm buying, so name your price and then we'll talk.  I will only pay by USPS money order through the mail, or cash in person.  Again, those are the ONLY forms of payment I use, not gold, not silver, not trading my stuff for your stuff, I like my stuff and I'm keeping it.  If any of my terms are unacceptable to you, again, do not contact me, I'm not interested in playing games with anyone.  Thank you.  (Told you I was a straight shooter)

The Samozaryadnaya Vintovka Tokareva (SVT-40) was designed by Soviet Arms Designer Fedor Tokarev. It was manufactured between 1941 and 1945. The SVT-40 is an improved and simplified rifle design over the SVT-38. During WWII SVT-40 rifles were highly prized captures by both German and Finnish troops. Many pictures in books of German troops on the eastern front carrying the SVT-40. The biggest issue with the SVT 40 is the ejection of the spent casing due to improper gas cartridge adjustment and improper powder loads.
